If you encounter the following error, *despite* having installed the NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit: 
it probably means the CUDA-related libraries haven't been properly added to your ```$PATH``` for some reason. A quick solution is to simply add this at the end of your BASH2* or BASH3* (replace the paths with wherever you installed the toolkit and change the version number accordingly): 
    export PATH=/usr/local/cuda-9.2/bin${PATH:+:${PATH}}
    export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/cuda-9.2/lib64${LD_LIBRARY_PATH:+:${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}}
